election.

00:52.452 --> 00:56.657 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mark Shields and David Brooks
analyze a full
week of news.

00:56.690 --> 01:03.597 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
All that and more on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:03.630 --> 01:06.466 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:06.500 --> 01:14.808 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Call it an
October surprise.

01:14.841 --> 01:19.680 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today's FBI statement about
Hillary Clinton's
e-mails roiled the presidential
race, just

01:19.713 --> 01:22.482 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
11 days before the election.

01:22.516 --> 01:23.784 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Donald Trump pounced.

01:23.817 --> 01:26.586 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Clinton camp demanded more
information.

01:26.620 --> 01:28.855 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Lisa Desjardins begins our
coverage.

01:28.889 --> 01:34.828 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Hillary Clinton
landed in
Cedar Rapids, Iowa to campaign,
but was greeted

01:34.861 --> 01:40.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by the news that the FBI is
reviewing newly
found e-mails linked the private
server she

01:40.133 --> 01:42.369 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
used as secretary of state.

01:42.402 --> 01:48.542 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a letter to congressional
chairmen, FBI
Director James Comey said: "An
unrelated investigation

01:48.575 --> 01:52.646 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
turned up e-mails that appear
pertinent to
the Clinton case."

01:52.679 --> 01:57.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He said he agreed with his team
to allow investigators
to review the e-mails and
determine whether

01:57.851 --> 02:02.589 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
they contain classified
information, as well
as assess their importance.

02:02.622 --> 02:08.261 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The candidate herself didn't
respond to shouted
questions, and didn't address it
at her rally,

02:08.295 --> 02:10.197 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
sticking with her stump speech.

02:10.230 --> 02:13.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HILLARY RODHAM CLINTON (D),
Presidential Candidate:
Everyone working across the
state are going

02:13.400 --> 02:15.602 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to make sure that we win Iowa.

02:15.635 --> 02:17.537 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

02:17.571 --> 02:21.041 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Clinton's
campaign chairman
did send out a statement this
afternoon calling

02:21.074 --> 02:26.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
