people feel like they are being
revictimized.

28:18.964 --> 28:26.071 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so the bill is an effort to
say that survivors
of sexual assault should have
certain rights

28:26.104 --> 28:30.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
under our criminal justice
system, and they
should know what those rights
are, and they

28:30.108 --> 28:33.045 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
should be treated -- everyone
should be treated
fairly.

28:33.078 --> 28:38.650 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is something that is
overlooked in the
law the way it exists now.

28:38.684 --> 28:46.458 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And so it was really her
advocacy and her
determination that has raised
this issue,

28:46.491 --> 28:51.763 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and gives us all of those
supporters around
the country who can help us talk
to other

28:51.797 --> 28:54.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
